cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about creating a benchmark for evaluating multiple object tracking methods in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves analyzing the state of the art in tracking methods, which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves testing and evaluating different tracking algorithms, which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
